# Admin Backend + Frontend Integration Plan

## Goal

Connect all admin pages (currently using hardcoded mock data) to real backend API endpoints backed by the `db_admin.sql` schema that is already applied to the database. This covers:

- **Dashboard** – real KPI stats
- **Users** – real user list with status, last login, token usage
- **Workspaces** – real workspace records
- **Knowledge Base** – real documents (upload + list + delete)
- **Analytics** – real aggregated token/session data
- **Audit Logs** – real audit_log rows
- **System Settings** – real `system_settings` key-value store
- Sessions page already connected ✅

LLM integration is explicitly **excluded** – token counts will be 0 until the LLM is wired up later.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [NEW] `backend/app/models/admin.py`
New SQLAlchemy models for tables added by `db_admin.sql`:
- `Workspace`
- `Document`
- `DocumentChunk`
- `SystemSetting`
- `AuditLog`
- `AnalyticsDailySummary`

Also update `User` model to include new columns: `status`, `last_login_at`, `updated_at`.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/app/models/chat.py`
Add missing columns to `ChatMessage` (`prompt_tokens`, `completion_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `response_time_ms`, `status`) and `ChatSession` (`ip_address`, `updated_at`), `ChatAttachment` (`session_id`, `user_id`).

#### [NEW] `backend/app/routes/admin.py`
Single consolidated admin router with these endpoints:

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | `/api/admin/dashboard` | KPI stats (users, sessions, KB docs, tokens, avg response) |
| GET | `/api/admin/users` | List users with filters + token aggregation |
| PUT | `/api/admin/users/{id}/status` | Change user status (active/inactive/disabled) |
| POST | `/api/admin/users` | Create new user |
| GET | `/api/admin/workspaces` | List workspaces with stats |
| POST | `/api/admin/workspaces` | Create workspace |
| PUT | `/api/admin/workspaces/{id}` | Edit workspace |
| GET | `/api/admin/documents` | List KB documents |
| POST | `/api/admin/documents/upload` | Upload KB document |
| DELETE | `/api/admin/documents/{id}` | Delete KB document |
| GET | `/api/admin/analytics` | Analytics data (token usage by workspace, top users) |
| GET | `/api/admin/audit-logs` | Audit log list with filters |
| GET | `/api/admin/system-settings` | Get all system settings |
| PUT | `/api/admin/system-settings` | Bulk update system settings |

A helper `log_audit()` function will write rows to `audit_logs` automatically for mutations.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/app/main.py`
Register the new admin router.

